						<summary>

						<p>This is dated on the 278th day of the 10th year of the king. It registers the gift made to the temple, of a golden image of Umāsahita weighing 1172 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi>, together with the pedestal and aureola, by the senior queen Pañchavaṉ-Mahādēviyār. Refers to one Kuḻalūr-uḍaiyār as the Supervisor of the temple at the time.</p>						

						</summary>
